    • Method Detail

      • ofSupplier

        public static <S,F> Result<S,F> ofSupplier(Supplier<Result<S,F>> supplier)
        Creates a new lazy result based on the given result supplier.
        Type Parameters:
        S - the success type of the result
        F - the failure type of the result
        Parameters:
        supplier - the function that supplies the actual result
        Returns:
        the new lazy result
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if supplier is null
        See Also:
        LazyConsumer.of(Consumer)
        API Note:
        The supplier is not allowed to return null or throw any exceptions. If it does, then the lazy result will relay the thrown exception (or NullPointerException) to its caller when/if it needs to be evaluated. If the lazy result needs to be evaluated again, it will throw NoSuchElementException (instead of trying to invoke supplier again). This ensures that supplier will be invoked at most once.

      • ofCallable

        public static <S> Result<S,Exception> ofCallable(Callable<S> callable)
        Creates a new lazy result based on the given callable. If the given callable produces a success value, returns a new successful result with it; otherwise returns a new failed result with the exception thrown by callable.
        Type Parameters:
        S - the success type of the result
        Parameters:
        callable - the task that produces a success value, or throws an exception if unable to do so
        Returns:
        the new lazy result
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if callable is null
        API Note:
        The callable may throw an exception, but it is not allowed to return null. If it does, then the lazy result will relay a NullPointerException to its caller when/if it needs to be evaluated. If the lazy result needs to be evaluated again, it will throw NoSuchElementException (instead of trying to invoke callable again). This ensures that callable will be invoked at most once.
